article.headline: Iona 69, Canisius 58
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. -- Freshman Scott Machado scored 15 points and was one of four Iona players in double figures in the Gaels' 69-58 victory over Canisius on Friday night. Milan Prodanovic had 11 points for Iona (7-9, 2-3 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), and freshmen Trinity Fields and Jermel Jenkins added 10 points each. Tomas Vazquez-Simmons scored 16 points on 6-for-9 shooting from the field for Canisius (5-10, 0-5). Greg Logins added 11 points and 13 rebounds, Elton Frazier had 12 points and Frank Turner 10 as the Golden Griffins lost their third straight.
